reviews.text: My family loves going to visit the local museums when they come see me and this is my little brother's absolute favourite. In the Civil War exhibit, there's a 360° movie that I've now seen at least three times all the way through and a couple times some of the way through, but every time I see it, I see something new. If flashing lights or gunfire cause reactions for you, you're better off avoiding the movie, but there's still plenty to see. I loved the parts that focused on medicine in the 1860s. There is an entrance fee and it'll be more if you're not a Kenosha resident. The gift shop has some amusing gifts but also period-appropriate pieces, like hat pins, for instance. There's a huge parking lot and it's right on the lake within walking distance of more entertainment and food. I think my absolute favorite room was the library upstairs. My daughter's favorite place was probably the balcony upstairs - outside. Beautiful views of the lake (with a picturesque lighthouse straight ahead) and a great place for her to get out some "wiggles," as she says.
This is great museum for a history class or just by yourself. There is so much information to take in all in one visit, I recommend going multiple times.
Absolutely loved it. Very unique Museum. It is actually Interactive. I thoroughly enjoyed it and highly recommended it.

This is a wonderful museum to bring students as part of their Civil War unit at school. The instructors are very knowledgeable and the program they created for the kids is very good. The 360 degree theater was amazing! I also love going to the gift shop for the unique items they get from WI crafters and businesses.
A great interactive museum! I thoroughly enjoyed the short time I was able to spend there, and think it is great for all ages.

Do you have a hour of time to waste then this is the best place to go. Not only do you learn more about the area but the exhibits never get old from looking at the fossils to the amazing view on the second floor, to the new ecology exhibit.

Its counterparts the Dinosaur, History, and Civil are also must sees  every single one making you think and realize how small in comparison to the universe you really are and how time has shaped us.

Awesome little local museum, showcasing the history of Kenosha. It's free to the public, they just ask for a donation of your choice. The upper floor offers artwork by a few different people that they change frequently. Entertaining for kids and adults. The gift shop is also very good

Had a blast at the museum! There are a lot of fun displays (both fossils and dioramas) and also a lot of informative literature posted everywhere for the adult or active learner! Nice gift shop and children's play area. Clean bathroom as well.

Great little place to learn about native people of the Midwest. The have large scale dioramas of native people with explanatory signage. Also, some good fossils from the ancient earth. Dramatic stone wall in the large entry area is a big architectural plus. Their donor wall on the second floor is sharp. Glass squares of varying sizes based on donor. I used to work in fundraising, so that was interesting to me. And, free!!

I love the Kenosha Public Museum.  I really enjoy the natural exhibit - the displays are nicely done and well thought out.  The artwork exhibits they have are really exceptional - I really give them a lot of credit there.

Good food for the price.  Seniors like the menu and value. Family restaurant with great seafood chowders. Their fish is well cooked and if you like meatloaf you'll be happy. Desserts are home made and yummy. Handicapped accessible.

The wait staff was cheerful and helpful.  We arrived shortly before closing time and stayed a little past.  The food was very good, especially the sweet potato fries.  I would recommend them without hesitation.

Second Best Boss I've ever had. First was my grandmother. All in all excellent food and service with a timely fashion. Great place for reservations and parties! Always Fresh Seafood,Steaks,Burgers,Chicken,Chowders and even Pasta. Weekly Specials and a large variety of desserts! Beers,Wines and even the Captain Him self! Great place for Fresh Maine Boiled lobster/Baked Stuffed lobster and other great dishes! Stop in and see for your self!

Service took forever - we got there before numerous other customers who received their appetizers before us. Waitress didn't come in to check on us or explain the wait time. Also worth noting our party wasn't particularly large, consisting of 4 people. My sister had a fly in her soda. When the food finally arrived, it was mediocre at best. Would highly not recommend.

GREAT Service but the whole lobsters were gone by the time we got there. Not all was lost as I got at least the 'Lazy Lobster' dish which was very good. I loved the homemade root beer too. Very rich and tasty.

Been here a couple times and the food, drinks and atmosphere are really good. It is a bit pricier, and it is not an "authentic" style Mexican restaurant. It is meant to be a little more unique. You can taste that everything is made fresh, even the tortillas, which in my opinion is what makes the whole taco at this place. My wife from California says Big Star is the closest thing that reminds her of home.

Came here with my brother on Valentine's Day just for a quick bite. We expected the place to be crowded and moving slow due to the holiday. Our experience was the complete opposite! Amazing service, fast, fresh, and a fun staff. At a point my brother and I order tacos and counted down from 30 to see of the service would stay the same. The tacos arrived by the time we hit the last 10 seconds.
Really enjoyed the tacos and queso at Big Star! Super fast service and good customer service. Definitely one of the better taco spots to check out!
Solid tacos excellent drink list. I like cocktails here. Fast services when sit at the bar. Pretty hard to find the parking on weekends.

On one hand, this place offers very good food, great in taste and and high in quality. Service was good, considering that Saturday afternoon during our visit the place was packed, yet we didn’t have to wait for the table. Fish tacos are a must try, they were pretty amazing. On the other, they lack a verity of beer, considering that there is a full bar. Overall, I’d say that it’s a little bit overpriced for the quantity of food, but I am likely to go back.

Good food. Fries were excellent (sweet potato and regular): not soggy at all and had just the right amount of salt/seasoning. Decent portion sizes. Malts/shakes were good too. Service was great as well.

Great food and not just burgers, the salads and wraps are absolutely amazing! Great craft beer and wine pairings. Friendly service and just an all around great atmosphere.. I would highly recommend checking it out and support this “truly” local establishment!!!!

A relaxed restaurant with a pretty good selection of beers.  Nice mix of regular and pub tables.  Decent amount of TV's to catch a game.  It's hard to ignore what is on the specials board as you walk in because it always sounds delicious and delivers, too.
Absolutely best food around. This town doesn't deserve this food. Great service great food!!!! Good kid's menu. A family fun good meal.
Fantastic service!! Very diverse selection of beer and burgers, and tasty weekly specials. This place is wonderful!!!!

Worth your while. Two of us had fish-I had the special and one person got German special. This is where you go to experience what a special dining experience was like back in the day. Rolls, pate and slaw go to each table and meals all come with very nice salads and soup. For me it was a lot of food but it was all very good. Service was great and we love the ambiance. Make sure you stop at the bar for an after dinner drink! Outside patio too is nice weather permitting. Hope this place will endure for many years to come!
We thoroughly enjoyed this place. The food was delicious and the service was amazing. I highly recommend!!

We have been there once in the past and our experience was terrible. Tonight we only went because we had a gift certificate that we wanted to use. We called and made our reservation, showed up 15 minutes early. We were shown to the bar since our table was not ready and we were early. The drink at the bar was called a poinsettia (amazing by the way). As our table came available we were sat promptly. Our waitress was so kind and took great care of us. The food was great, the drinks were great, the service was exceptional!!! We will definitely return.
Swank bar, excellent service, worth every penny. Love coming here for a couple appetizers and cocktails in the bar. Highly recommend.
Food and service are amazing. Great authentic German food. If you don't have the money to travel to Germany to eat this is the next best thing. You have to try the liver pattae.
Once a week I go here as a treat and have gone through and ordered everything on the menu over the past 6 months. Everything is VERY good and always fresh. It's my go to for a quick bite now
It's ight. Don't get the burger though, one of the worst burgers I ever had. Fires were good though no cap. It's meh.
1.00 hardshell tacos you can't go wrong

Called to place an order and the women was rude as well as lied about what they have on the menu.  I ate there a lot and know what's on the menu, why lie and say you never had it. I won't eat there again.
My hubby loves Mexican food
Love this place!! We have never had a bad experience. Food is always great and service is always great.

The decor is fun with lots of cool knick knacks to look at. The people who work there are friendly. The salsa was awesome. The cheese enchilada was very good. The restaurant is clean and the people work hard. The taco was bland and lacking seasoning. The chips, while tasty, seemed stale and lacked that snap and crunch I expected. The cheese dip was bland and lacked spices. The night we were there, they were quite busy and service was slow and subpar. Drinks, chip refills and special requests such as sour cream came out very slowly.

I gave them a 3 because I think my visit this time was average, not exceptional nor terrible. I would eat there again. Many of the issues I mention above are correctable; it is entirely possible that on another visit I would have better service and more seasoned food and would then give this restaurant a much higher rating.
Awesome food and service. Great clean atmosphere. Great staff and the manager was very hospitable and friendly.
Amazing food at great prices! What more can you ask for?!?  The staff is always courteous. The portions are good sized and fill you up. 😊

Best Mexican restaurant in town! The food is always fantastic. The atmosphere is great. The staff and ownership treat you like family. Rarely is there an issue with your order and the service is fast! It’s great for a quick work lunch! Try the cheese dip!

Soon loves spending time with her guests and adds so much to the experience despite the difficulty understanding her sometimes. She remembered me and I was an infrequent guest! The food is amazing and better sushi than anything I've tried in Milwaukee Chicago (yet2019) I have yet to find a better place and I am LOOKING! The atmosphere is usually quite despite the small dinner room and is really nice for dates, its casual dress but still feels like you could go with a nice button down and jeens

Soon's is the BEST Sushi joint EVER!!!  If you are looking for atmosphere, you will not find it here.  But if you want EXCELLENT fresh generously portioned Sushi,  friendly staff and owners...this is where you want to be!!!  I usually get the regular sashimi and Squid salad (always ask for the fish egg garnish.....AMAZING!!!!).  My husband usually gets a couple rolls and squid salad.  Soon and her husband Bob always go to the tables to welcome you and make sure your visit is a good experience.   If it's your birthday...make sure you make it known.   Soon makes a homemade fish cake.   Not what you expect with s name like "fish cake"... it is masterfully made by Soon for her birthday guests and is absolutely delicious!!!! If you don't like sushi... they have other non-cash choices.  :-)  Make sure you check this place out...you won't regret it!!

Soons is delicious. Sushi is always fresh and mouthwatering. The ginger dressing they make for their salad is an amazing thing on its own. Bob and Soon make you feel like family. Great atmosphere and delicious coma inducing food.

Tried this place in Kenosha quite a few times now and it is pretty good. The Korean Bibimban rice dish served in a very hot bowl. It has sauteed seasonal vegetables, and either chicken or beef with a hot sauce on the side. There is little fried egg in it also. Very good. We always also order some different sushi, and the last we had is a keeper, so good. It was like a shrimp tempura sushi and was terrific. We also always get the usual California roll and one other to try. All are great.

Went there with a group of three. Two of us ordered hot dishes, the third ordered sushi. Apparently there absolutely ZERO understanding of how to prioritize portions of an order so EVERYTHING can come out at once. The two hot dishes came out at the same time, and in a reasonable amount of time, even with the place being a bit busy. 35 minutes later, after the other food was very cold, the sushi had still not arrived. What sort of nonsense is that? When talking to the "waitress" about it, her response was to act in a manner I'm probably not allowed to describe accurately on here, but essentially she was EXCEPTIONALLY unprofessional. Needless to say, I have zero desire to ever return.

My husband and I received a gift card here and were excited to try it out. The atmosphere and decor was nice and modern. It also seemed clean. However the food was not good and it was extremely overpriced in our opinion for what we got. We spent a decent chunk out of our own pocket after the gift card was applied which hurt a little. We will not be coming back after this experience.

Nice local family friendly food place with a bar area for others to watch a game or have a drink.  Can be extremely busy at times and hard to get a table since it is pretty limited seating.  Would love to see a rooftop patio built (fresh air seating when warm/closed-in seating when cold) to enjoy views of the lake year round.

Good food, fast service , although we were there at about 3:30 on a Saturday. The entrees are pricey, some of their items are unique, my kids love their Pizza. The only thing I didn't care for is we were waited on by at least three different servers during our visit there. all in all a nice place and we will definitely be back.

Good and timely service bellied-up to the bar on a busy lunch on St. Patrick's day. Good selection of tap beers; menu has regular fare and seasonal specials. BBQ pork on burger did have quite a bit of fat (instead if meat), so choose carefully.

Fantastic service, food was fantastic very clean and friendly place. The only problem we had was very noisy so i wouldn't take a 1st date here if i wanted to have a conversation.  But I really like the place!!
Great pizza! We only ever do carry out, but the staff is friendly and we are always guaranteed fast service. Don't forget to try their tiramisu! The prices aren't to shabby either. Highly recommend!

Cute,very clean restaurant with a quaint bar.  Friendly outgoing staff. Pizza was fast, hot and delicious.  Met a few lovely chatty other customers. Many other guests were enjoying the fish fry and said it was amazing and a cute hidden gem of a place. We will definitely be back!

I ordered food here before, and it was pretty decent. It was somewhat overpriced, but the food was good, and they deliver. However, today my son has been vomiting, and I ordered a two liter of Sprite with my grilled cheese sandwich anhey forgot to add the two liter to my order. After they didn't add it to my order they said it's only $3 and will send it out right away. I consented and I proceeded to wait another half hour before I called back. Now I'm waiting again and my son is still puking. The girl taking the order was inattentive. The delivery driver did not embark right when they said he would. I live literally a mile away from this place. Very disappointed.
Everything was good got in right away, food was good people were nice

A true family restaurant as I sat there and observed the owner interacts with everyone and I saw how everyone is treated like family. That is very hard to find now a days .I highly recommend this place. The food was pretty amazing and their drinks we had the Kentucky burban porkchop and they were delicious. Also the drinks are great and I thought it was very reasonable what we payed for dinner. Also as a side note I would like to say that they have honest employees I left my wallet and completely forgot where I had left it. They were very prompt and honest and returned it that shows the integrity that this business has. I really appreciated and will definitely recommend to all of my friends and family.

A pilot friend flies 100 miles to join us at the Coffee Pot. I would like to think it is to be with me and my wife but I know better. He comes for the food. The Coffee Pot makes an outstanding breakfast - I've had many of the dishes on the menu. Forgive me for not having pictures nor a review of specific dishes - they are ALL good! Amazing breakfast. Great bloodies too. Service is great. Usually packed in the mornings but that means it's good!

This place rocks! We've driven past this joint a million times. Never payed it any mind. Then, a week ago, we stopped in. Boy oh boy was it tasty! Fresh ingredients used to concoct the most raddest, maximum quality breakfast. Dig it baby!

I had the best breakfast of my life this morning! I'm not even much of a breakfast person, but my wife is. We visited and split a Breakfast Buster Sandwich and Eggs Benedict with salmon. Both were absolutely incredible, but I have to say that I left my heart with the sandwich. We will be visiting again!

Superb breakfast and lunch diner, open for decades and decades. Very busy on the weekends but turnover is fast, you won't wait long. "New" takes on old favorites - try the "Reuben Omelet."  They offer thick sliced toasted from baked in-house bread. Their off the bone ham is marvelous. I'll be back.

It is a little more expensive than some places but it is VERY well worth it! Very large servings. They only take cash. There is an ATM if you need to use it. Also, I was very pleased to see that they have expanded seating into the space to the North of them. And, in the appropriate weather, there is outdoor seating.

My wife and I stopped by for lunch. It has a large variety on the multi page menu so it  should have something for everyone. It looks like a nice neighborhood family diner. Great food and very good size portions so you won't leave hungry. I generally don't have extra to take home but I was full and had a little to take home. I recommend this as a nice stop when in Kenosha.

You’re definitely full when you leave here. Ample portion size. Friendly and prompt service. I had the Tommy’s Home Run skillet. Delicious! My daughter had the Strawberry Crepes, very large amount. Normally the order comes with three, one crepe would be plenty for a child or an adult who fills up quick.

Our waitress was sweet. The food was really really bad. I ordered the stuffed chicken and rice. It looked and tasted like cheap microwaveable chicken cordon bleu and the rice was like instant rice. It came with mixed veggies which were not fresh but definitely canned mixed veggies and it all tasted horrible and left a horrible after taste. My fiance ordered a burger....the meat was so dry and super flat. He said it almost tasted like jerky with no flavor. This place could have the potential to actually cook good good from scratch instead of cheap microwaveable food that I wouldn't even eat at home.

Wonderful, as always. Parking lot and sidewalks clear of snow and ice, restaurant clean, staff friendly and efficient (also helped each other as needed) as well as keeping an eye out for coffee refills, food good n quick.
Love to come in for breakfast and lunch. Friday night fish fry is fantastic.
Good tasting bread made daily at a good price.
Best Italian bread you can buy
Friendly place with quality products!
There is not a lot to choose from at this bakery.  There is mostly the same type of bread that you could buy at any grocery store.
Love this place and staff. Excellent everything is very delicious.
We came up to visit our family in the Chicago area.  The kids wanted us to go to Paielli's Bakery for treats.  Excellent and friendly customer service.  The goods are SO delicious!
Very busy on Christmas Eve but they got you through fast. Very efficient friendly staff.

Amazing bakery! I've been coming to this bakery for ten years. Greats baked goods! Donuts, cakes, Kringle, cookies, breads, it's all here and for a great price. 2 dozen donuts for $20.00 great price for quality desserts/pastries. Refirgertors with drinks and dough to purchase. Open at 6:00 am. Great friendly service. Highly recommend coming here!
I had no idea I lived so close to this amazing bakery. Everyone was nice and they had a great selection.
Great selection of bread and bakery items at a relatively low price! We no longer live in the area but when we visit we tend to make a stop for at least a loaf of Italian bread and a few donuts!
